# Android-only (permanent)

Fluent Mobile ships **Android only**. There will never be an iOS app. Do not add iOS config, assets, CI, scripts, or documentation unless the user **explicitly** requests iOS.

## Prebuild

Always pass **`--platform android`**. Never use `--platform all`, `--platform ios`, or omit the platform flag.

```bash
npm run prebuild
# equivalent: expo prebuild --clean --platform android
```

Do not commit generated `android/`. Ignore `ios/` — it must not be generated or maintained.

## Bootsplash / native assets

Generate Android assets only:

```bash
npx react-native-bootsplash generate assets/bootsplash/logo.png \
  --platforms=android --background=0b50d0 --logo-width=100
```

`assets/bootsplash/android/` is required. iOS bootsplash assets are not used — do not add or regenerate them.

## EAS

Use **Android profiles only** in `eas.json` (`development`, `preview`, `production`). Do not add iOS build profiles unless explicitly requested.

```bash
npx eas build --profile development --platform android
```

Tag releases (`v*`) trigger `.github/workflows/eas-build.yml` + `.eas/workflows/create-production-builds.yml` (Android production only). See [`.eas/README.md`](../../.eas/README.md).

## Development

| Command | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `npm start` | Metro |
| `npm run android` | Dev client on emulator/device |
| `npm run prebuild` | Regenerate `android/` only |

Do not run `expo run:ios`, `npm run ios`, or iOS simulators. `Platform.OS === 'ios'` branches in shared UI are fine when they improve Android layout.
